whoami => tells usernam
touch meri_file.txt => make new file
ls => list 
pwd => present working directory
cd test => change directory to test
cd => typed only cd and hit enter then you'll be at home directory.
mv ../meri_file.txt . => Be in directory where you wanna copy and this command will only move the file from previous directory.
cp => works similar like mv, to copy files.
clear => clear the terminal
nano => editor runs on terminal
nano meri_file.txt => opens this file on terminal
cat meri_file.txt => display content of file on the terminal.
echo => is the print command of linux, needs to double quotes.
history => gives list of last entered commands.
ls -la => Gives detail of the file.
rm meri_file.txt => To remove files.
